Hello! I am an acclaimed writefag, long thought dead, emerging from hibernation and probably will be dead after I finish these next two stories. There seems to be a discussion on wholesomeness vs emotional conflict. I am pretty much the master of this.
>Oh Yeah? What did you write faggit
That doesn't matter right now. What matters is this:
Wholesome is perfectly fine, probably preferred actually. Most people on here probably want to read something where the writer is very good at describing in vivid detail and originality just how comfy it is to cuddle into some fur. If there is true emotional weight to the story, it's sole purpose is to make the "cuddle moment" more sublime, and that's it. Any drama is a tool to guide the reader into what they are really looking for and should be treated as such.
However if you want to write a "serious" story involving "serious" issues. I'd recommend you don't, unless you're confident that you're actually a good writer. Because in the hands of the unskilled this can devolve into edgy sadness for the sake of it. Which I both loath and have been accused of perpetuating myself. There's got to be some soul behind the suffering or it's just shallow sadomasochism. This is incredibly hard to describe how to do properly but it's incredibly easy to see that sort of thing for what it is when you read it. Frankly, you either got it, or you don't (or you just need to get experience writing).
Anyway, I've been told Wetchop is a fan of my work, so I'm hoping what I'm working on next will blow so many minds that I'll get fanart for free, because I'm both poor and cheap.
